Generic single-database configuration for Alembic migrations.

## Usage

### Create a new migration
```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"
```

### Apply migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Rollback one migration
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### Show current revision
```bash
alembic current
```

### Show migration history
```bash
alembic history
```

## PostgreSQL Migration

This project uses Alembic for database schema migrations from MySQL to PostgreSQL.

### Initial Setup
1. Ensure PostgreSQL is running
2. Update DATABASE_URL in .env
3. Run: `alembic upgrade head`

### Creating Migrations
Alembic will auto-detect model changes and generate migration scripts.
Always review generated migrations before applying!
